caption: I love Sam's Falfel. Freshly made right in front of us. Very delicious. There is a small queue during lunch hours. Fast serving. Platter and Sandwich are available.

Best falafel in the city, hands down! Always good quality ingredients, made with love. When the coronavirus first hit New York and my org started working from home, I was saddest to lose my weekly ritual of visiting Sam and his wonderful employees for my $5 falafel pita lunch. These guys truly know what they're doing. There's a line for a reason y'all - and it's worth the wait.
Best street falafel I've ever had
best falafel in lower manhattan
(Translated by Google) One must-eat after Zuccotti Park is falafel. It is a taste that reminds me of dumplings in Korea.  (Original) 주코티 공원 지나면 꼭 먹어야되는 개쩌는 팔라펠입니다. 한국의 만두 생각나는 맛인데 속이 꽉차있고 구성짐
This is the best falafel in the city, and cheap! And with lots of delicious hummus, peppers, and roast eggplant on the side if you get the platter! Easily the best lunch option in the area.
Been here for 30 years rain or shine. Its delicious, thank you

This place has delicious fresh homemade falafel.  They are fast and cheap for this expensive locale.  I always get their falafel sandwich and it is loaded with falafel, roast eggplant, delicious hummus and salad.  Very satisfying lunch for under $10.
Food was mediocre The glob of beige slop was flavorless The falafel were ok The dolmas tasted like it came out of a can Underneath it all were cooked onions and iceberg lettuces
username: Honestly Name a better place if you have one

caption: Delicious falafel, amazing value at $5
Amazing food. This was the best falafel I have ever eaten!

I've tried 10+ different falafel restaurant and carts around the city, by a long shot, this is the best. The turnover that they have keeps the falafels fresh, crispy on the outside, soft on the inside. I love that they're more liberal with tahini than huumus, I love that there's eggplant as option, and I love their whole vibe! Pro tip: if you want a snack, it's $1 for 4 falafels with tahini on.
Always great food and excellent service.
Great prices, great service, amazing food! Very nice people, will be coming back.
I go three times a week, for the last 20 years. Never dissapoints

(Translated by Google) Awesome. If n words how good it is. Very cool those who attend, super friendly. It is the smallest cart in the whole square, without lights or anything. Do not miss it.  (Original) Impresionante. Si n palabras lo bueno que esta. Muy buena onda los que atienden, súper amables. Es el carrito más chico de toda la plaza, sin luces ni nada. No se lo pierdan.
Oh man! People were not kidding when they said that this is the best Falafel in NYC! Affordable and delicious
Best lunch deal downtown.....delicious.

Best falafels ever. If you're in downtown NY, you MUST try! The only thing missing is rice or a good, freshly baked pita. These guys serve ready to eat pita that definitely doesn't go well with the falafels.
I always stop here with my dog. We share a falafel. This is the best $5.00 meal you can find. Get some hot sauce added. The line moves quickly.
We happened to stop by this cart and get a falafel wrap to eat and was so glad that we did as it was the best , the yummiest falafel wrap I ever had in my life !!!
Tasty food with nice white sauce
Its a must visit place for us everytime we are in NYC. The most delicous falafel with hummus we have ever tasted. Greetings from the Czech Republic!

We had a platter for $7 and a $5 sandwich. Drinks are $1 each. Everything is inclusive of tax! No faffing around! The food was absolutely delicious and can be eaten without appetite. If you are not hungry go for the sandwich as the platter is served very generously. A few minutes after we got our food, the queue was big! The staff is very helpful and patient with newbies. Definitely recommend it!
Among other things, Sam location has been in the same spot for over 20 years.... AWESOME SERVICE. GREAT FALAFEL. THIS IS A MUST TRY.

I'm from Egypt and this place is as good as it gets in terms of falafel. It's so authentic and delicious and the price is amazing. You get a heap amount of food for $7 or an amazing sandwich for five dollars. You can't beat that
Very good falafel and at  a good prices
Good vegetarian option, flavorful falafel sandwich, great service!
Very good!
Amazing falafel

Starts with one liner "awesome and freshness"  Really awesome, everything on the platter is completely fresh. The falafel are so fresh along with the salads and the fresh hummus makes it an excellent platter. They add pickle and some sort of leafy rice(rice inside spinach leaf i guess) which makes richer. Try the platter and sandwich.

This is, without a doubt, the best falafel in all of New York City. Everything about their sandwich and platter is just perfection. And the price is unbeatable. Plus, the guys are some of the friendliest you’ll find—you could not be supporting better people. Make sure to ask for some pita chips with your order. They hand-make them at their cart and they might be the best pita chips I’ve ever had. Seriously, eat here. You won’t regret it.
Fresh,cean and big portion. Really good and  tasty
The falafel platter is the best value around.
Soooo good

This is the best HOMEMADE Egyptian food in the area!! I also love that they are family owned and so so friendly! Best take out food too! So convienent and casual- this place is now my go to when I can’t cook! I highly highly recommend you all try it- every single dish is absolutely delicious!!!
Best falafel I’ve ever had. Get the platter, Sam really hooks it up
The best falafel platter I've ever had.  Far superior to any other falafel cart or restaurant for that matter.  Truly fresh falafel.   I will walk far to visit this place.
incredible food, super reasonably priced, great portions and the guys are so great, they always have a smile on their faces!
Great one
Great and tasty falafel for a good price!
This is easily the best falafel in nyc. Spiced perfectly, they make it homemade and on the spot.
The food is super delicious and its cheap. It’s a great value for money.
Can’t beat this veggie lunch for the buck. Once a week fixture for me
Killer falafel, compares well to the places in Paris that have a wait 10x as long
Got a great hot dog for fair price.
Good food at a good price. Supersize for a buck more.
The best place for falafel in NYC
Really amazing food cart! The falafel was the best one we ever ate!
Great food served from heart.. They're awesome.
Good food
Best falafel in Financial district. No other place can beat $5 for a falafel sandwich or $6 for platter
Absolutely delicious. There may be a 20 people line at Sam's cart and one or two people at the cart beside which also sells Falafels. It's incredibly delicious and you should get an extra to go ;D
The best falafel sandwich in New York. Hands down. Every time I go it’s better than I remembered. They could charge triple and I’d keep coming back
Can't beat the price/quality/quantity equation at this Zuccotti Park institution. Always a line, but it moves fast.

Best food cart value by far. For $6 you get a falafel combo platter filled with falafels, grilled vegetables, humus, tahina, salad and hot peppers, along with a pita. It's seriously about 2-3 lbs of food and can be shared by 2 or 3 people (or 1 fat slob like myself). And quality of the food is as good as the quantity.
Love these guys, great service, amazing food and for a reasonable price. No matter if there are 2 or 20 people in line, it's always worth the wait.

Falafal is nice Veggie food that you can enjoy while roaming around in NY streets. Sam's Falafal is best Falafal maker in the NY. If you are in NY and u havent tasted it, then u must.  I bet it will soft your hunger.
Been eating here for 20 years. So good! The falafel balls are crispy and the white sauce is legit. Pro tip: don’t be fooled by the imposter cart next to Sam’s. Check out my picture.
The guys working here are very nice. Food is great too. I get extra falafel for a dollar. I was extremely full. And i usually eat a lot.
This is the best falafel that I've had in NYC, and it comes at a reasonable price. The falafel balls are soft and moist, and the sandwich is extremely flavorful.

Top flight food cart that does one thing - falafel - and does it very well. Fresh, flavorful, crisp falafel made expertly minutes before being added to a pita or platter. $5 for the former and $6 for the latter is eminently reasonable. This cart is well worth an extra walk from points throughout the financial district. Pass on the many mediocre alternatives on your way. You won’t be disappointed.

These guys have the best Falafel allover new york city.... Actually they have he best Falafel allover the World. I am Middle Eastern and i haven't tasted Falafel as delicious as the ones they are doing... Great job Sam's Falafel keep it up.
Very good and large falafel at very reasonable prices.  Line is often big but moves quick.
Best falafel in the city. These guys are my brothers from another mother!
I love this. For $6, taste is really good and platter is heavy for lunch. People are good too. Mostly it's crowdy in lunch hours. Go early as possible.
When I visit NY, I make a point of visiting this cart. Best falafels.
Absolutely perfect for someone on a budget. Taste great!! I go here 2-3 times a week for a falafel.
This is by far the best felafel we've ever eaten and the owner was so friendly and gracious! We'll be back to NYC just to eat here again!
So good. Amazing deal.
Best place ever!!! Greatest!!!
Great guy. Awesome food!

First time, have a falafel sandwich from this cart. The falafel are freshly/swiftly balled up and fried. Crisp, hot, and good. I have walked past many times but I have been discouraged by the line, I hate waiting on line for food. The line moved quickly, though. The falafel sandwich was good and I got everything I wanted in it. Many falafel stuffed way down in the bottom of the sandwich, so don't get discouraged if you only see 2 on the top. You have to eat this sandwich with a fork, it is so much food packed into a pita if you try to go for a big monster bite the ingredients may end up on your clothes or floor.
Best in town
(Translated by Google) Exquisite! Of the richest I ate in recent years.  (Original) Exquisito!  De los más ricos que comí en los últimos años.
Nice guy..
Best falafel. I love this place. Eating for more than 10 yrs same place same food.

One of the best if not THE best Falafel in NYC and the US. Delicious, fresh, rich, vegetarian, clean, and incredibly inexpensive. Sam is friendly, generous and professional. His $5 is a complete meal for a big eater. I drive all the way from Virginia at least once a year to enjoy his Falafel.

There is almost always a long line at Sam's during lunch, so you know you are getting good food.  Their falafel sandwich is one of my favorite in the city, and it's a sizable portion to feed a hungry dude for only $5.
